# Colors Contract (Strict Control)

- Colors will be provided explicitly by you; do not generate or suggest new colors.
- Do not modify provided colors.

## Semantic Tokens Only

- Components must use only semantic color tokens (example names: `primary`, `background`, `text`, `muted`).
- Do NOT use raw Tailwind palette color utilities (example: `text-green-500`, `bg-blue-200`).

## Dark Mode (Paired Definitions)

- Semantic colors used in the UI must be defined for **light** in `src/styles/tokens/semantic-aliases.css` and for **dark** under `.dark` in `src/styles/tokens/dark-mode.css`.
- When adding a new semantic color, add both the `@theme` entry and the `.dark` override in the same change; do not ship a token that only works in light mode.

## No Fallbacks (Critical)

- Do NOT fallback to raw Tailwind colors under any circumstance.
- If a required semantic token is missing:
  - request it rather than using any fallback
  - do not invent an approximate semantic token name

